  "about": "Johann is a German male given name. It is derived from Iohannes, which is the Latin form of the Greek name Iōánnēs (Ἰωάννης), itself derived from Hebrew name Yochanan (יוֹחָנָן‎) in turn from its extended form Yehochanan (יְהוֹחָנָן‎), meaning \"Yahweh is Gracious\" or \"Yahweh is Merciful\". Its English language equivalent is John. It is uncommon as a surname.",
  "note": null,
  "source": "dark_horse"
